<div class="os-eob os-solution-container" data-type="composite-page" data-uuid-key=".solution7"><div data-type="solution" id="fs-idm118463568-solution"><a class="os-number" href="7-exercises#fs-idm118463568">1</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-solution-container">
<p id="fs-idm32049296">The protons in the nucleus do not change during normal chemical reactions. Only the outer electrons move. Positive charges form when electrons are lost.</p>
</div></div><div data-type="solution" id="fs-idp63165504-solution"><a class="os-number" href="7-exercises#fs-idp63165504">3</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-solution-container">
<p id="fs-idp81646832">P, I, Cl, and O would form anions because they are nonmetals. Mg, In, Cs, Pb, and Co would form cations because they are metals.</p>
</div></div><div data-type="solution" id="fs-idm94727984-solution"><a class="os-number" href="7-exercises#fs-idm94727984">5</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-solution-container">
<p id="fs-idm110255632">(a) P<sup>3–</sup>; (b) Mg<sup>2+</sup>; (c) Al<sup>3+</sup>; (d) O<sup>2–</sup>; (e) Cl<sup>–</sup>; (f) Cs<sup>+</sup></p>
</div></div><div data-type="solution" id="fs-idm69463840-solution"><a class="os-number" href="7-exercises#fs-idm69463840">7</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-solution-container">
<p id="fs-idp109450000">(a) [Ar]4<em data-effect="italics">s</em><sup>2</sup>3<em data-effect="italics">d</em><sup>10</sup>4<em data-effect="italics">p</em><sup>6</sup>; (b) [Kr]4<em data-effect="italics">d</em><sup>10</sup>5<em data-effect="italics">s</em><sup>2</sup>5<em data-effect="italics">p</em><sup>6</sup> (c) 1<em data-effect="italics">s</em><sup>2</sup> (d) [Kr]4<em data-effect="italics">d</em><sup>10</sup>; (e) [He]2<em data-effect="italics">s</em><sup>2</sup>2<em data-effect="italics">p</em><sup>6</sup>; (f) [Ar]3<em data-effect="italics">d</em><sup>10</sup>; (g) 1<em data-effect="italics">s</em><sup>2</sup> (h) [He]2<em data-effect="italics">s</em><sup>2</sup>2<em data-effect="italics">p</em><sup>6</sup> (i) [Kr]4<em data-effect="italics">d</em><sup>10</sup>5<em data-effect="italics">s</em><sup>2</sup> (j) [Ar]3<em data-effect="italics">d</em><sup>7</sup> (k) [Ar]3<em data-effect="italics">d</em><sup>6</sup>, (l) [Ar]3<em data-effect="italics">d</em><sup>10</sup>4<em data-effect="italics">s</em><sup>2</sup></p></div></div><div data-type="solution" id="fs-idm117401984-solution"><a class="os-number" href="7-exercises#fs-idm117401984">9</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-solution-container">
